cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about neural language models and their ability to store and retrieve knowledge. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The use of pre-trained models and fine-tuning suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the evaluation of performance on open-domain question answering tasks relates to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the mention of model size and scalability suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be a relevant sub-category.
